"Drinkability – A very interesting and unusual stout that I enjoyed."
"From bottle to cold glass. Pours a dark reddish brown with creamy head. Complex aromas of chocolate, spices and coffee. Feels much lighter than many other stouts.  The flavors are diverse, with the most noticeable being the slightly bitter coffee rounded out by the sweat and creamy chocolate. Notes of spices remind me of drinking Mexican hot chocolate. Overall a fantastic beer with lots of flavors that balance beautifully. One of Stone's best."
""
"Very impressed with this beer's cooperation. Ingenious blend of chocolate and spices that creates a well-balanced taste. If you like this, you might want to also check out Clown Shoes' Chocolate Sombrero."
