"O-  The first time I had this, I was expecting a normal mocha stout, not a mocha stout with Mexican chocolate!  This is a lot better knowing what to expect going in!"
"Poured from 22 Oz into snifter. Quite a nice find for my little western PA bottle shop. Midnight black with little to no head. Some slick, transient lacing. A beauty. Lots of pepper/green pepper on the nose, with some nice cinnamon, nutmeg, coffee, dark chocolate, cocoa... ridiculous. If they said it was there, it was. The spices were prominent in the taste, an overarching pepper note (sans heat), and some nice chocolate. Velvety mouthfeel, with some of those lovely, lingering spices. Delicious. The reason that I love craft, and a terrific homebrew inspiration."
"A little light but very nice coffee notes.  A LOT of great Coffe stouts out there and this is a damn good one for sure!"
"Dark brown body, 2 finger head with minimal lacing. Aroma of peppers and cinnamon leaps out. Flavor has peppers with even bit of heat and lots of cocoa. Body is thin though and affects drinkability a bit but overall i still enjoyed this."
