""
"22oz bottle served in a tulip.  Pours the color and clarity of cola with a loose, 1/8th inch, khaki-colored head embedded with tiny ringlets that quickly disperses into a broken sudsy skim.  Some small spots and swaths of lacing are revealed during the tasting.  Nose expresses cocoa, cinnamon, nutmeg and just a hint of chili pepper.  Taste follows nose with  a hint of oxidation and more baker's chocolate than cocoa.  Mouthfeel is light-medium in body with an assertive carbonation that, coupled with the chili peppers, leaves a mild, residual burn at the back of the throat.  Overall, a decent beer but I don't understand the hype on this one."
