"Overall, this is an absolutely delightful beer.  SO…MUCH…cinnamon!!  This is true across both the aroma and the flavoring, where it meets, as it does so well, with a white sugar sweetness.  This makes the beer very, very “cinnamon-sugar”.  Otherwise, the quality of the beer is outstanding.  Each advertised flavor is so perfectly represented, with nothing seeming to cheap out, and nothing seeming synthetic or false.  All of this makes the beer disappear so quickly.  In the parts where we purchased this, there was a widespread one-bottle minimum, so we had to split our efforts.  We ended up getting only one bottle on that first day of the release here locally, but as soon as we could, picked up a second, once that wave came through.  Now, after tasting it, we are infinitely glad we did, but simultaneously kind of sad that we didn’t get any other bottles.  Alas, oh well, but perhaps stone will re-release this one as an ultra-anniversary beer, and it will once again humble us in its presence."
