"Pours a deep black with tons of sandy-tan head that held pretty well and faded into decent lacing, good wisps and a medium collar.  Aroma is chocolatey, a grainy medium malt, lots of nutmeg and cinnamon, a hint of indistinct earthy spice (peppers/chilis).  Taste is bitter coffee up front, nutmeg and vanilla playing well together, and a malty sweetness.  Nice warmth from the peppers, kinda high carbonation for a stout and definitely thin in the body.  Good beer, but lacks in too many ways to be great."
