"Pours pretty black, some caramel highlights at the bottom of the glass.  The head is short, but nicely creamy, dropping to a bubbly band and patchy film.  Big, deep, spicy aromas waft out of the glass...cocoa, vanilla bean, cinnamon, nutmeg, dark coffee beans, nuts, chili peppers - pretty much exactly as advertised and well executed.  Flavor opens with a smooth blend of dark cocoa, cinnamon, and nutmeg followed by vanilla and a pleasant fruitiness.  Not particularly spicy, but the chili flavor is there in a supporting role.  This beer is really more about the spices and malty mocha flavors than the heat.  Chocolate pudding, whipped cream, and berries.  Medium-full bodied and sort of fluffy, drying out completely and not allowing it to get too sweet.  Nicely done."
"M: Extra smooth, melted chocolate, and not too sticky. Soft, almost heavy, and in general whipped up."
