"Bottle from trade and shared with the wife. Pours dark brown from the bottle and settles nearly black in the glass with a two finger khaki brown head. Honestly looked on the thin side as it poured. Aroma is big on the chili peppers, cinnamon and nutmeg, with hints of chocolate and vanilla in the background. Don't get a lot of roast or sweetness in the nose though. Flavor is a different story with lots of cinnamon and chocolate, kick of peppers, a hint of vanilla, and lingering nutmeg. Too much vegetal pepper and some metallic notes. Not spicy really, just vegetal flavored. Medium plus bodied, smooth, with medium plus carbonation. As expected from the look, this is on the thinner side for the style. Needs that big sweet depth to stand up to the spices, but is lacking that. Overall this isn't a poor beer, but it's pretty disappointing after having Mexican Cake, Hunahpu, Abraxas, Bomb, and barrel aged variants of all of those. This one really isn't close."
