"Yes, this was strong but the alcohol could only be felt and not tasted. The transition from fall into winter involves the Marzens and Pumpkin Ales giving way to Stouts and Porters and if any beer could bridge that divide, this would certainly be it. The spice reminded me of a Pumpkin Ale without the burn while the body of this beer was clearly a Milk/Sweet Stout that wasn't jacked up on lactose and sugar. If you love beer, get this. It's not the best Stout out there and probably the best seasonal currently on the shelf but it's damn close to being either of those and the most unique brew that you could grab before the winter firmly sets in. A wonderful mesh of flavors could be found here as this easily deserves to be added to Stone's full-time rotation. A subtly fabulous brew that pushes the boundary of what's possible while tasting as familiar as the recurring seasonals that don't quite measure up to this."
