"Pours a solid black color with a solid two finger frothy tan head that shows great retention. Aromas of coffee, caramel, and chocolate dominate with the spicy peppers poking through a bit especially as this warms. The nutmeg and cinnamon are subtle but again poke out a bit more as my sample warms. Great Aroma! Rich chocolate and vanilla hit my palette in spades. Coffee and pepper sweep in to cleanse the sweet maltiness. Milk chocolate with spices linger with a sweetness long after the end of every sip. Medium to thick body with a light to moderate level of carbonation and a creamy silky velvety mouthfeel. Damn there's a lot going on in this beer! Creamy rich flavorful brew, so glad I was able to find some of this!"
