""
"Overall I thought this was a good beer and a good example of the style, I found this to be pretty close to Oddsides Mayan Mocha Stout and it had pretty much all the aspects that I look for in the style.  This beer had nice drinkability, it was fairly smooth, crisp, slightly creamy, a little dry on the finish, a little filling and the taste did a nice job at holding my attention, I think one bottle is the perfect amount for me.  What I like the most about this beer was the aroma, it was very good and to me it was the highlight of this beer.  What I liked the least about this beer was the higher level of bitterness, I wouldn't mind less bitterness with just a little more sweetness, I would buy this beer again and I would recommend it to anyone who likes spiced Stouts.  All in all I was happy with this beer and just a little impressed, stone can be pretty hit or miss for me, but this one was pretty close to being a hit.  It's not my favorite stone beer and it's up there with one of my favorites of the style.  Good job guys, this was a tasty beer, keep up the good and creative work."
