"22 ounce bottle, bottled on 08/29/14.  Served in a DFH snifter, the beer pours dark brown/black with a half inch tan head.  Both the head retention and lacing are good.  Aroma is nice, the brew smells like coffee, peppers, bittersweet chocolate, cinnamon, and some vanilla.  I think the taste is pretty much just like the aroma, but there's also some nutmeg and vegetal pepper flavors.  The peppers seem spicer in the aroma, there isn't much pepper heat in the taste of this beer at all.  Maybe I guess I was just expecting it to be spicier.  With that being said, I still think it's a pretty tasty brew!  Mouthfeel/body is medium, it's a bit coating and creamy with a good amount of carbonation.  I liked this a lot, especially the coffee/mocha/chocolate flavor.  Stone and the other collaborators hit a home run with this, hopefully Stone will decide to bring it back at some point.  $9.99 a bomber."
