"Overall (4.25), this might be one of Stone's best beers to date. I'm obviously predisposed to like it, given the style and ingredients, but I still think they have executed it quite well. They've managed to capture my favorite parts of the big Mexican stouts, while making it unique enough that it's not just a knockoff of other beers. I know it's not often that Stone decides to redux a collaboration beer, but I'm really hopeful that they will decide to produce this one regularly. Even if not, I have made sure to stock up on bottles--an easy thing to do at such a reasonable price with such wide availability."
