"In a word, impressive.  This style - Mexican hot-chocolate/coffee - has become increasingly popular in recent times, with a number of breweries exploring this flavor combination. What Stone has created is an absolute beauty of a coffee/hot chocolate/cinnamon/pepper stout.  Without a question this is the best beer from Stone that I've tried and easily deserving of a place in the list of my the top 5 stouts. I can only hope that they decide to bring this back on a regular basis, as it would regularly find its way into my refrigerator.  At $8.99/22oz, this surely has to be a more economical and equally delicious alternative to the likes of a number of hard-to-find, brewery-only Mexican-hot-chocolate-style stouts.  If you can find a bottle or two, go for it - I only hope I can get my hands on a couple more."
