"Bottle. Pours black. Light is too feeble to pierce this brew. The head was initially a huge, airy, puffed and brown in color. It dies off to a very thin ring that has leaves long lacing islands. What an interesting aroma. Coffee and cinnamon really come out. The pepper spice is right there, too. The flavor is less dynamic but I actually prefer its more rounded flavors. I'm happy the peppery heat isn't as intense. It's got some excellent mocha and coffee and chocolate. The cinnamon is as soft as the pepper. Vanilla is also detectable. Body matches the octane pretty well. Medium to soft carbonation. Far more drinkable than I was expecting. I wasn't overly in love with the flavors but I liked it well enough. New Stone offerings keep me and many like me come ping back and back and back."
