"Poured from a bomber into a schooner, the beer is a dark, almost jet black coloring, with mahogany highlights around the edges, and a tall, dense, foamy, light tan head that slowly settles into a tight surface coating.  Beautiful.  The aromas are toasty and cinnamon forward, with subtle chocolate and mocha coffee in the background.  It almost smells like a chai latte.  Nice. Flavors are heavily roasted forward, with a blast of coffee and dark chocolate, as well as a healthy dose of cinnamon.  Some pepper heat slips in the background, not to overpower, but to enhance everything.  Vanilla highlights help round everything out, too.  Pretty layered and rich palate.  The chocolate and subtle heat join the cinnamon spice in the aftertaste.  This smooth, slightly dry brew provides a smooth, almost creamy finish, with a cinnamon and roast linger. Some of that coffee bitter lingers, too. Great beer!"
