"Jet black with a rich brown head. Very little lace as I drink it and head retention is minimal. Smells strong of chocolate. More milk chocolate than dark. The taste is hard to describe. So much going on here. Some chocolate with a lot of spices and sweet vanilla. The spices (maybe nutmeg) take over but not in a bad way. Tastes like Christmas eve. Creamy mouthfeel that is close to thick chocolate milk. Overall, an incredible beer. So unique and complex. So much going on, but nothing really fights for attention. Everything just falls into place. Definitely one I will be seeking out to stock and store."
