"Overall: This stout is not one to be missed. It is definitely a seasonal stout. The nutmeg and cinnamon shine through but this is a chocolate dominant stout. A lot of times chocolate/milk stouts go terribly wrong due to too low of an ABV or too high. At ~8% this offering is alluring and satisfying. This is not a BIG stout, or something akin to an Russian Imperial, as the drink-ability is astounding! This fluffy and tasty collaborative stout is one of a kind."
"O - Really awesome creation of a Mexican hot chocolate-coffee-beer-thing. Love the lower ABV, drinkability, balance of all-around great flavors. Just pure tasty goodness, great as a autumn breakfast and/or dessert beer. This will probably be a repeat purchase for me this season."
