"Poured into a Fremont small snifter. Pours pitch black, appearing opaque in the glass, with a half finger light brown head with good retention and lacing. Very aromatic, dominated by Mexican chocolate (with the cinnamon typical of this style of chocolate), coffee, sweet dark malt; spicy and appealing. Flavor is sweet dark malt, lactose, light Mexican chocolate and coffee, pie spices, lightly nutty. Nice medium creamy body. Amazingly well balanced, with the spices and milk stout components complimenting each other perfectly and a nice note of coffee in the background. This could have easily been dominated by any of the strong flavors, but everything is in harmony. ABV well covered; this could be a rich chocolate infused horchata. Recommended."
