"Pours a deep black with khaki head. Aroma is a potent blend of coffee, chocolate, and cinnamon, with the spices becoming more prevalent as the beer warms. The flavor falls a bit flat unfortunately; way thinner than expected. I get the coffee up front and the cinnamon lingers in the finish but I was hoping for something a bit more rich and complex. Almost no pepper or vanilla flavor. The body is also lighter than expected, which helps drinkability but kind of takes away from the experience. I had very high hopes for this and can't help but feel slightly let down. Don't get me wrong; this is a very good beer, especially for the price, but of the similar-style beers I've had this year I'd have to rank them Mexican Cake > Hunahpu > Xocoveza > Bomb!"
